The paper deals with reachability oracles for directed graphs, which is a fundamental problem in computer science. The transmission graph is a specific type of directed graph that arises in wireless communication networks, which is a topic in the subfield of computer networks (cs.NI). However, the paper focuses on the algorithmic aspects of the problem, which are more closely related to computational geometry (cs.CG) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also involves some combinatorial and probabilistic techniques, which are relevant to discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and numerical analysis (cs.NA). Finally, the paper presents experimental results and comparisons with other algorithms, which are typical of simulation and modeling (cs.SI). Overall, cs.CG and cs.DS are the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.DM, cs.NA, and cs.SI.
